) by grey-ochreous tint to the wing coloration, by more contrasting wing pattern (wider and always clearly expressed medial line, usually having brown diffused shadow on inner side), by a smaller and more uniformly colored reniform spot, and by the absence of an orbicular spot in most specimens. In male genitalia the new species differs by having a narrower valva that is more deeply constricted medially at the ventral side, and by the shape of the proximal extension of the aedeagus and shorter proximal part of the aedeagus (coecum).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
